Project Overview
This project is a SaaS platform that integrates with the Shopify API to provide a dashboard for viewing and managing orders. Users can register, log in, and view key metrics about their Shopify store, including total orders, total sales, and conversion rates. The dashboard features an automatic refresh mechanism.

Architecture
The project follows a MERN stack architecture, utilizing the following technologies:

Frontend:

React: A JavaScript library for building user interfaces. The dashboard and authentication components are built using React.
React Router: For navigation between components (login, registration, dashboard).

Axios: For making API requests to the backend.

Backend:

Node.js/Express: The backend server handles authentication and Shopify API requests.
MongoDB: Used for storing user data and authentication information.

API Integration:

The project integrates with the Shopify API to fetch order data for display in the dashboard.
Setup and Installation

To set up and run this project locally, follow these steps:

Clone the Repository:


git clone https://github.com/Rishabhkhandelwal333/Shopify-Dashboard.git
cd shopify-dashboard
Install Dependencies: Navigate to both the frontend and server directories and install the necessary dependencies.

bash
Copy code
# Frontend
cd frontend
npm install

# Server
cd server
npm install

Set Up Environment Variables: Create a .env file in the backend directory and add the following variables:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_uri
SHOPIFY_API_KEY=your_shopify_api_key
SHOPIFY_API_SECRET=your_shopify_api_secret
Start MongoDB: MONGO_URI

Running the Project
Start the Backend Server: In the backend directory, run:
npm start
Start the Frontend: In the frontend directory, run:
npm start

Access the Application: Open your browser and go to http://localhost:3000 to access the application.
